### Cross-service expand: remote → local. A DELEGATED entity with backlink
### associations to LOCAL entities. The Customers consumption view declares
### three local backlinks:
###
###   notes : Association to many CustomerNotes       on notes.customer = $self
###   tasks : Association to many FollowUpTasks       on tasks.customer = $self
###   risk  : Association to one  CustomerRiskRatings on risk.customer  = $self
###
### When the client asks `$expand=notes,risk`, the plugin strips those items,
### forwards a pure Northwind query for the customer(s), then queries the
### local tables for matching rows and stitches them back in.
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Customers('ALFKI')?$expand=notes,risk

### Same pattern on a list — works for multiple parents in one request.
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Customers?$top=5&$expand=notes,risk&$select=customerId,companyName,city

### Mix cross-service expand: remote → local with delegated expand (remote →
### remote). Here `buyer` expands into the Northwind Customer for each order —
### a pure remote → remote expand handled by CAP — while the outer query is
### still a delegate on Orders.
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Orders?$top=3&$expand=buyer($select=CompanyName,Country)
